This paper discusses a machine learning algorithm for nonlinear manifold learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a generic formulation of embedding algorithms and studies their relation with spectral methods and graph Laplacians. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of embeddings in computer vision (cs.CV) and social influence analysis (cs.SI), which are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a strategy for faster training of the algorithm, which could be relevant to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE).
